  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Promoting Peace among Internally Displaced Persons,  Returnees, and Host Communities in Mali</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project supports communities and local authorities in hotspot areas of Mopti and Timbuktu regions of Mali to mitigate tensions, promote peaceful cohabitation and enhance means of livelihood. IOM and its partners are identifying conflict-prone areas, as well as the specific variations and drivers of conflicts, and working with local communities to identify and implement solutions. The project also contributes to fostering positive relationships between local communities and the police force in the Diboli border area with Senegal and at the Sona border with Burkina Faso.</narrative>
  </description>
